  "rule_text": "Use only the approved gradient set; never invent gradients. Approved gradients are Brand Blue \u2192 Dark Navy for dark backgrounds and blue mastheads/waves; Sky Blue \u2192 Deep Blue for blue backgrounds and waves; Sunshine \u2192 75% Gold for warm backgrounds; Golden Sand \u2192 White \u2192 Light Blue for soft light backgrounds; Golden Sand \u2192 75% Gold \u2192 Sunshine for warm light-to-saturated backgrounds; and Sunshine \u2192 light gold for the logo-mark masthead. In masthead/banner applications, gradients run horizontally from dark/saturated to light, left to right as shown. Use gradients as backgrounds, with the wave graphic, and with the LISRAYA logo mark; the logo-mark masthead uses the Sunshine (#faa31b) \u2192 light-gold (\u2248#ffe05c) gradient, with the mark at the lightest end for contrast.",
  "intent": "Preserve the approved gradient palette, directional treatment, and logo-mark contrast treatment.",
  "source": "design_bible",
  "doc_ref": "color_scheme_rules[3]",
  "group_id": "grp_lisraya_color_scheme_rules_03",
  "status": "active",
  "version": 1,
  "summary": "Use only approved gradients per background type with specified colors and horizontal left-to-right direction; include Brand Blue\u2192Dark Navy for dark, Sky Blue\u2192Deep Blue for blue, Sunshine\u219275% Gold warm, Golden Sand\u2192White\u2192Light Blue soft light, Golden Sand\u219275% Gold\u2192Sunshine warm light-to-saturated, and Sunshine\u2192light gold for logo-mark masthead with mark at light end."
